modules.description: Provides functions for sending HTTP requests, handling responses, and managing connections, with support for custom headers and body parsing. Works with types such as `request`, `response`, and `uri` to enable low-level network interactions. Used to build client-side logic that integrates with web services or APIs, such as fetching data from external endpoints or submitting form submissions.

This module facilitates HTTP request handling, WebSocket communication, and message parsing, operating on structured data like URLs, headers, bodies, and connection streams. It leverages a type alias for HTTP methods to enhance clarity in defining request semantics, enabling modular interaction patterns. Use cases include building real-time web applications, managing asynchronous data transfers, and customizing HTTP workflows with precise method definitions.
